This two script prepare data for moving to tapes:

1: first sort data into time-steps:
$ python tarScripts/sortSnapshots.py path_to_snapshots_produced_by_bonsai  snapshot_prefix 
e.g.
$ python ../tarScripts/sortSnapshots.py ./  MW 

2: Tar files:
$ python tarScripts/tarSnapshots.py  path_to_snapshots_produced_by_sortSnapshots split_size_in_GB
e.g.
$ python tarScripts/tarSnapshots.py  ./MW 200

3: copy folder ./MW.tarball to tapes


To unpack:
$ cd ./MW.tarball
$ xf 00000.0000/archive.tar -F ./newVolumeScript.sh 
Preparing volume 2 of 00000.0000/archive.tar.
Preparing volume 3 of 00000.0000/archive.tar-2.
Preparing volume 4 of 00000.0000/archive.tar-3.
Preparing volume 5 of 00000.0000/archive.tar-4.
..
$ rm -rf 00000.0000/archive.tar*  [to remove archive files and create free space]


Note: newVolumeScript is generated by tarSnapshots.py inside ./MW.tarball


